<P>
The last interview with martyred Brazilian rubber tapper Chico Mendes is 
included in "Chico Mendes: Voice of the Amazon," a one-hour documentary that 
will be screened during World Rainforest Week at the Nuart Theatre in West Los 
Angeles. The film shows at 4 p.m. weekdays and 11:30 a.m. Saturday and Sunday. 
Actress Linda Hunt narrates film, which also is slated for airing on TBS cable 
Nov. 1 at 7:05 p.m. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
